===Countering Madness===
Bringing [[Inventory blocking food|food that leaves an item behind]], such as [[Guthix rest]], [[curry]], and [[summer pie]]s, will force the Chaos Elemental to never use its Madness attack, as it cannot unequip the player's items if there is no room in the inventory to do so. Players who have completed [[Alfred Grimhand's Barcrawl]] should also disable vial smashing via the [[barbarian guard]] or through the game settings as well, so that finishing a potion will leave the vial behind.

This does, however, give the Chaos Elemental a chance to use its Discord and Confusion attacks in turn, so you could leave just a single empty spot in your inventory for the Chaos Elemental to unequip one of your items instead of up to four. With enough practice this can save some supplies in the long run, since its Madness attack does not deal any damage and replaces the potentially high-hitting Discord attack.

Another strategy to prevent this attack from being launched is to bring a sack (or basket) of potatoes, cabbages, onions, etc. Whenever you need to eat, simply empty the sack or basket after each bite. With practice this can be done quite quickly without interrupting your attacks. Additionally, if you leave an open inventory slot and wait for its Madness attack to be launched, you can empty the sack before the attack lands to fill the empty inventory slot and negate the effect, guaranteeing a zero damage attack.

==Solo Flinching Method==
[[File:Chaos Elemental safespot.png|thumb|The dead trees at the south-west tip of Rogues' Castle can be used to flinch.]]
[[File:Chaos Elemental safespots.png|thumb|Stand in the tile marked 1 as the Chaos Elemental spawns. As soon as it spawns, run to the tile marked 2. The Chaos Elemental will only be able to make one attack against the player, and will then get stuck by the flinching safespot.]]
The safest method for soloing would be taking advantage of the hit-and-hide tactic (also referred to as [[flinching]] or hit-and-run which is a melee-only method) with the usage of nearby trees. This can be done by attracting the Chaos Elemental's attention, and then immediately running behind a tree so it can't attack you. Wait for its [[Hitpoint]] bar to disappear, hit it once, and run back behind the tree. Repeat until the elemental is dead. This method can be done with any [[Melee weapon]]. A full set of [[Verac's equipment]] is recommended for fast kills, but you '''WILL''' [[Items Kept on Death|risk]] the [[Verac's helm]] if you get [[smited]] by a [[PK]] team.

An alternative, 3-item-safe layout could include a melee weapon with high stats (disregarding attack speed)- a [[Godsword]], [[Dragon warhammer]]+[[Defender]] or [[Dharok's greataxe]], along with 1-3 extra items to boost offensive bonuses, plus some cheap prayer-boosting gear such as monk robes for the times when offensive prayers and [[Preserve]] might be active.

If not using the hit-and-hide tactic, using a [[Karil's leathertop]], [[Verac's helm]] and [[Verac's plateskirt|plateskirt]] with a [[Crystal shield]] or [[Dragonfire shield]] and a [[Rune crossbow]] or [[Armadyl crossbow]] with [[Diamond bolts (e)]] makes this boss very easy to kill, even at sub-100 [[Combat level]]s, but beware of the risk. As there's a strong chance to encounter [[player killers]], it would be better to stick to lower-cost gear to alleviate the risk.

==Solo Safe Spot Method==
[[File:Chaos elemental safe spot setup locations.png|thumb|Mark the tiles on the left first and then the right second. They should all be on the same north/south line. The image on the right is not oriented north.]]

You can also set up a safe spot where you can freely attack the Chaos Elemental without it being able to attack you back. To use this method efficiently, you will need to mark a column of tiles running north to south, near the [[Wilderness Resource Area]]. 

The northernmost tile to mark lines up with the north-easternmost Yew tree (left image). Staying on this line, run all the way south to the Wilderness fence and mark this southernmost tile (right image). This tile line is the farthest west the Chaos Elemental can attack. 

Now, with the Chaos Elemental near its spawn by the Rogue’s Castle, aggro it and then run straight south to the Wilderness fence. (There is a 2x2 tree near its spawn you can hide behind to avoid a few hits as you lure it south). With the Chaos Elemental still trying to attack you, run west along the Wilderness fence—staying as close to the fence as possible—until you reach your marked tile. Wait here until the Chaos Elemental catches up to you. As soon as you see the Elemental, run directly north. Once you get to your two northernmost tiles, stop and wait for the Chaos Elemental to catch up to you again. [[File:Chaos elemental safe spot complete.png|thumb|alt=An example of how it will look when using this safespotting method. Note the marked tile is on the same north/south line as our other marked tiles|An example of how it will look when using this safespotting method. The player can attack the Chaos Elemental, but the Chaos Elemental will not fight back. The marked tiles are on the same north/south line as the previously marked tiles.]]When you can see the Chaos Elemental, run directly towards it. You can do this by attacking it. As you get close to melee range, step one tile to the west and attack the Chaos Elemental from its western side. If you have done this correctly, the Chaos Elemental will be floating on your tile line (which, again, is as far as it can roam or attack) and the player will be one tile west of that line. At this point, you can freely attack the Chaos Elemental and it will never attack you back as long as you do not cross back over the tile line.    

It is important to note that the red teleportation attack when running from the southern to northern tiles can teleport you west of the attackable line. If this happens and you're not able to re-aggro the Chaos Elemental before it starts resetting, you may have to wait for the Chaos Elemental to return to the spawn area and restart the lure entirely.

This method can be very useful for lower-leveled or lower-geared accounts (such as irons). It can take some practice and trial and error to set up, but once the lure is complete you can finish the kill almost entirely AFK and much faster than flinching every hit with a tree.

You should plan to bring food with you, as you will be attacked by the Chaos Elemental on average 10 times during the setup. Even low healing food, such as Tuna, may be sufficient.

If you have access to stamina potions or energy potions, they can be useful if you have to restart your lure, as this method does require a lot of run energy.

==Team==
